  "prompt": "Why do I feel such disgust towards being in a relationship?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons for feeling this way:\n\n1. Past negative experiences\n- Previous toxic or traumatic relationships\n- Heartbreak or betrayal\n- Witnessing unhealthy relationships\n\n2. Psychological factors\n- Fear of vulnerability\n- Low self-esteem\n- Trust issues\n- Attachment anxiety or avoidance\n- Commitment phobia\n\n3. Personal preferences\n- Valuing independence\n- Enjoying single life\n- Prioritizing personal goals\n- Not feeling ready for emotional investment\n\n4. Emotional protection mechanisms\n- Fear of getting hurt\n- Self-preservation instinct\n- Past emotional wounds\n\n5. Potential underlying issues\n- Unresolved trauma\n- Depression\n- Anxiety\n- Past childhood experiences\n\nRecommended steps:\n- Self-reflection\n- Consider therapy\n- Process past experiences\n- Work on personal healing\n- Understand your emotions\n\nEach person's feelings are unique, and there's no universal \"right\" way to approach relationships. Understanding the root of your feelings can help you navigate them more effectively.\n\nWould you like to discuss this further or explore any specific aspect of your feelings?",
